            <title>[KAFKA-12537] Single Threaded applications will not work with SHUTDOWN_APPLICATION</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-12537</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Single Threaded EOS applications will not work with the streams uncaught exception handler option SHUTDOWN_APPLICATION. This is because the EOS thread needs to close and clean up, but to send the shutdown signal it needs to have at least one thread running.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
